<TITLE> Train-truck collision disrupts Sylhet-Dhaka-Ctg communication </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Moulvibazar, June 29 (bdnews24.com)--Train communication got disrupted early Friday in Sylhet-Akhaura section of Bangladesh Railway following a collision between a truck and the Sylhet bound Surma mail. Mohammad Jahangir, assistant station master of Srimangal railway station told bdnews24.com that the accident occurred at about 3:30 am at Teliapara level crossing of Sylhet-Akhaura route. The impact of the collision left the engine of Surma mail derailed and the truck totally crushed, Jahangir added. A relief train from Akhaura reached the scene early morning and started rescue operations. After the collision, Sylhet bound Parabat Express was stranded at Mantala, Dhaka bound Jayantika Express at Shayestaganj and Akhaura bound Kushiara express at Vanugachh railway station. Sylhet-Chittagong-Dhaka train communication remained suspended till 11:45 am, this report compilation hour. bdnew
